Just took another look. The only questions I have left are:

- Can you move MapVirtualColumn to a contrib extension? It seems kind of specialty and not a good fit for core.
- The `.` dot notation for embedding extra details in the column doesn't seem necessary to me; could it be replaced by adding that to the constructor of the virtual column?

In that case, VirtualColumn would become:

```java
/**
 * Virtual columns are "views" created over a ColumnSelectorFactory. They can potentially draw from multiple
 * underlying columns, although they always present themselves as if they were a single column.
 */
public interface VirtualColumn
{
  /**
   * Output name of this column.
   *
   * @return name
   */
  String getOutputName();

  /**
   * Build a selector corresponding to this virtual column.
   *
   * @param factory column selector factory
   * @return the selector
   */
  ObjectColumnSelector init(ColumnSelectorFactory factory);

  byte[] getCacheKey();
}
```

And MapVirtualColumn's constructor would become:

```java
  @JsonCreator
  public MapVirtualColumn(
      @JsonProperty("keyDimension") String keyDimension,
      @JsonProperty("valueDimension") String valueDimension,
      @JsonProperty("outputName") String outputName,
      @JsonProperty("targetKeyValue") String targetKeyValue
  )
```

And "targetKeyValue" would be used instead of the part after the dot in the column name. So if a user wants to get "map.k1" and "map.k2" as VCs, they would define two VCs, one for each.

Then we get virtual columns like.. (`VirtualColumns`)
```
  private final Map<String, VirtualColumn> withDotSupport;
  private final Map<String, VirtualColumn> withoutDotSupport;

  public VirtualColumn getVirtualColumn(String dimension)
  {
    for (int index = dimension.indexOf('.'); index >= 0; index = dimension.indexOf('.', index + 1)) {
      VirtualColumn vc = withoutDotSupport.get(dimension.substring(0, index));
      if (vc != null) {
        return vc;
      }
    }
    VirtualColumn vc = withDotSupport.get(dimension);
    if (vc == null) {
      return withoutDotSupport.get(dimension);
    }
    return null;
  }
```

@navis why is that loop needed? Would this work instead:

```java
private final Map<String, VirtualColumn> withDotSupport;
private final Map<String, VirtualColumn> withoutDotSupport;

public VirtualColumn getVirtualColumn(String columnName)
{
  VirtualColumn vc = withoutDotSupport.get(columnName);
  if (vc != null) {
    return vc;
  } else {
    // No VC without dot support matches this columnName; try ones with dot support.
    int index = columnName.indexOf('.');
    return withDotSupport.get(index < 0 ? columnName : columnName.substring(0, index));
  }
}
```

That's what I was imagining.

